  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "They modified the parent set pruning rules and the approach used to determine a high-scoring DAG for each order, in order to take account of ancestral constraints.",
    "Li and van Beek (2018) compared MINOBSx with a MCMC approach which also supports constraints called CaMML (Korb and Nicholson 2011), when learning well-known BNs of up to 48 variables.",
    "Li and van Beek (2018) found MINOBSx to be more robust than CaMML as it was always able to satisfy all the knowledge constraints specified.",
    "They noted that ancestral constraints reduced the number of arcs erroneously missing or mis-orientated in the learnt graph.",
    "However, ancestral constraints tended to encourage additional extraneous edges in the learnt graph."
  ],
